DRURY LEDBETER, 400 acs. Brunswick Co. adj. his own old line & Simms;
12 May 1770, p.12. £2.
JACOB MILLER, 200 acs. Mecklenburg
Co. on the brs. of Allen's Cr, adj. Hill;
12 May 1770, p.13. £1.

SHERWOOD WALTON, 850 acs.
Bedford Co. on the S side of Otter Riv.;
27 Aug 1770, p.124. £4.85.

THOMAS GRIFFIN, 179 acs. Sussex
Co. on the S side of the Copohonk Sw.;
adj. Thomas Alsobrook, the College
Line, Howell Briggs & Edward Wright;
27 Aug 1770, p.124. £1.

WILLIAM McCLUNG, 42 acs. Augusta
Co. on both sides the Cowpasture Riv.;
27 Aug 1770, p.173. 5 Shill.

PETER BIBY, 99 acs. Amherst Co. on
the S brs. of Owens Cr., adj. John Joslin;
27 Aug 1770, p.210. 10 Shill.

WILLIAM PORTER, 34 acs. Augusta
Co. adj. his own Land, his old Survey;
27 Aug 1770, p.211. 5 Shill.

SAMUEL BLACK, 65 acs. Augusta Co.
joining his own Land, his Patent Line;
27 Aug 1770, p.216. 10 Shill.

WILLIAM GATEWOOD, 130 acs. Amherst Co. on both sides of Buffaloe Riv.;
adj. James Freeland, Stanhope Evans &
Fry; 16 Feb 1771, p.246. 15 Shill.

JOHN AUSTIN, 190 acs. Halifax Co. on
a br. of Sandy Riv., adj. Roy & Morton;
16 Feb 1771, p.321. £1.

JACOB COGER, 94 as. Halifax co. on
both sides of a North fork of Mayo Riv,;
16 Mar 1771, p.432. 10 Shill.
